VETERAN actress Michelle Botes, who was better known for her villainous role as Cherel Hanes on the then SABC3’s Isidingo, will make an epic comeback to the small screen next month. The award-winning actress returns as Angelique Price on M-Net’s upcoming telenovela The Legacy. The telenovela has already set tongues wagging on social media. ALSO READ | JERUSALEMA REMIX GOES GOLD! The actress left Isidingo some years ago and went on to star in Binnelanders but since then, she has been under the radar. On the telenovela, she plays a bitter ex-wife who can’t accept that her ex-husband has moved with a new woman. The trailer for the telenovela is already out, and Michelle’s fans can’t wait to see what she has in store for them this time.